 15, 2021, Bumrah married model and broadcaster Sanjana Ganesan in Goa. Ganesan, a resident of Pune, Maharashtra, formerly competed in Miss India and participated in MTV's Splitsvilla in 2014. Juhika, Bumrah's elder sister, resides in Ahmedabad, India. Juhika got hitched to engineer Varun Celly in 2017. The closeness between the siblings is quite strong. Although sister no longer live with Bumrah in a family together after her marriage, they are still close and often meet each other in Ahmedabad. Physical Appearance Jasprit has an average height and weight of 5' 11" and 68 kg, respectively. He has a 38-inch chest and 14-inch biceps. He has black hair and dark brown eyes. Favourites Jasprit enjoys eating Dhokla. His three favourite batsmen are Virender Sehwag, AB de Villiers, and Sachin Tendulkar. Bumrah respects Zaheer Khan, Lasith Malinga, and Colin Croft. He enjoys watching Amitabh Bachchan on television. He also enjoys listening to music. About Parents Jasbir Singh and Daljit Kaur are parents of Jasprit Bumrah by blood. Jasbir was a businessman. Jasbir helped Santokh Singh Bumrah, his father, manage their three industries. Jasbir passed away when Bumrah was just five years old child. There aren't many photos of the father-son pair because Jasprit lost his father at a very young age.. Daljit Kaur Bumrah is the name of Jasprit Bumrah's mother. She was the headmistress of Ahmedabad's Nirman High School, where Jasprit had previously attended. The success of Bumrah has been greatly influenced by his mother. Bumrah has cherished playing cricket since he was a little boy. His practise, though, often interfered with his mother's afternoon sleep. Then, Bumrah's mother instructed him to play quietly around her. Bumrah then began bowling towards the floor skirting, which made less noise and finally assisted Jasprit in mastering the technique of bowling Yorkers. Relationship Sanjana Ganesan and Jasprit Bumrah were wed in Goa in March 2021. Bumrah took a break from playing in