ricket. He smashed 29 runs in a single over bowled by Stuart Broad and broke the Lara's record that almost stayed for 18 years. Records by Jasprit Bumrah In a bilateral ODI series of five or fewer games, Bumrah is the only fast bowler to record the most wickets (15 vs SL). In 2017, he created history by becoming the first Asian bowler to take five wickets in a single Test innings in South Africa, England, and Australia. He is India's second-fastest player to get 100 ODI wickets. Only three Indians have got hat-tricks in Test matches and Bumrah is one of them. He achieved his first-ever first-class half-century (55*) against Australia A team on December 11, 2020, while India was touring Australia. Awards and honours Selected by Cricbuzz for the tournament's IPL XI in 2017. Named by ESPN Cricinfo in the T20 XI for 2016 and 2017, and by Cricbuzz in 2017. Named by the ICC to the World Test XI for 2018. Named by the ICC to the World ODI XI for 2018. Selected by ICC and ESPN Cricinfo in their "Team of the Tournament" for the 2019 ICC World Cup. On January 12, 2020, Jasprit Bumrah was presented with the Polly Umrigar Award, the highest honour in Indian cricket. The Polly Umrigar Trophy is presented by the BCCI to the top male international cricketer. At the BCCI Annual Awards ceremony, he was given this prize for the best international cricketer (2018-19). In 2019, people saw Bumrah play in his first Test match against South Africa. The Dilip Sardesai Award was also handed to Jasprit Bumrah. Jasprit Bumrah Bowling Style Initially, Bumrah got famous due to his typical bowling style. He still has the same bowling action. Bumrah makes a brief run-up, the first few steps of which are short, like the staccato strides. He generates high pace with an odd stiff-armed movement, and the batters have a hard time reading his bowling because of his peculiar point of release. He frequently bowls short or outside the off-stump. Bumrah is known as one of the fastest Indian bowlers, outper